description:
&lt;p&gt;Newham CAMHS and London Borough of Newham have worked for many years in close partnership in order to provide an embedded CAMHS offer for a wide variety of LBN settings, including: Childrens Services, Special Educational Needs, Youth Offending Service, Secondary School/Headstart and Looked-After Children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is suitable for a specialist mental health practioner from a range of modalities, including but including Nursing, Psychology, Psychotherapy and Family Therapy and will require a registration to a equivalent professional body.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These services are overseen by a specialist Clinical Director and two Pathway Leads, one for LAC and one for Education and Childrens Services. The Education and Childrens Services Pathway Lead Postholder will be responsible for the coordination and management of the following embedded CAMHS Pathways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HEADSTART Secondary School CAMHS offer - providing direct consultation to the boroughs secondary schools and the boroughs HeadStart Service who will also provide a mainstream school link role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Special Educational Needs Offer providing input to 4 education settings (three PRU settings, one primary EBD setting and a specialist provision for young people with moderate and severe developmental and learning difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EARLY HELP &amp; CHILDRENS SERVICES OFFER providing input into Childrens Centres, Families First, and LBN Childrens Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Youth Offending Team offer providing a comprehensive embedded CAMHS role within Newhams Youth Offending Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job summary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Education &amp; Childrens Services Embedded CAMHS Pathway Lead will be a A 0.5 WTE Senior CAMHS Practitioner, leading this embedded CAMHS Pathway which encompasses the above mentioned teams which amounts to approximately 9.5 WTE CAMHS workers across all settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Pathway Lead will be supported by and work closely with the LBN Embedded CAMHS Pathway Clinical Director to support multi-agency decision making; outcome monitoring; troubleshoot any operational issues and provide clinical supervision and support to the embedded practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Supervision and Line management will be structured through a cascade model in which the 8B Pathway Lead will supervise Band 8A Clinicians and the Band 8A Clinicians will supervise the Band 7 Clinicians. The Clinical Director will Line Manage the Pathway Lead but Clinical Supervision will be provided by the appropriate Clinical Lead within CAMHS, matching the Pathway Leads core profession to a suitable senior clinician of that profession within CAMHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
